SIMPLE: wherein
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wherein
<hw>Where*in"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>In which; in which place, thing, time, respect, or
the like; -- used relatively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her clothes <qex>wherein</qex> she was clad.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There are times <qex>wherein</qex> a man ought to be cautious as
well as innocent.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In what; -- used interrogatively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Yet ye say, <qex>Wherein</qex> have we wearied him!</q>
<rj><qau>Mal. ii. 17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whereinto</ent>⟦br⟧
